URL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/6894#issuecomment-612237278


   @wesm the issue is implicit `move` on return: 4.8 will only do this if the return type exactly matches the returned expression:
   
   ```c++
   #include <memory>
   
   struct B {};
   struct D : B {};
   
   std::unique_ptr<B> works() {
     std::unique_ptr<B> up;
     return up;
   }
   
   std::unique_ptr<B> broken() {
     std::unique_ptr<D> up;
     return up; // should work; unique_ptr<B> is implicitly constructible from unique_ptr<D>&&
   }
   
   std::unique_ptr<B> workaround() {
     std::unique_ptr<D> up;
     return std::move(up);
   }
   ```
   
   This failure extends to `Result<unique_ptr<B>>`, which is implicitly constructible from `unique_ptr<D>` 

